    <title>Simpler reporting for small businesses: discussion paper</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Seeks views on simplifying reporting requirements for incorporated businesses. Looks at the prospects for developing a new reporting regime based on the minimum required that meet the needs of users through alignment with the tax system and reducing or removing inconsistencies. Aims to significantly reduce the regulatory burden on the very smallest businesses and release the associated cost savings. Consultation period ended 30 October 2011.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
